# 14. 失った笑顔

Tsukasa: So, you're the real Nene who was controlling that robot?
Nene: .....
Emu: Nene... It's okay, no need to feel bad.
Rui: I recharged the robot. It's fully operational again.
Tsukasa: .....
Tsukasa: You forgot to charge it... I can't believe my show was ruined all because of such a stupid mistake!
Nene: I'm...sorry...
Tsukasa: I don't need apologies!
Rui: Tsukasa, it's not like Nene did it on purpose. After we left yesterday, she stayed behind to rehearse until late.
Rui: It's partially my fault too. I forgot to check the battery before the show. Next time, I'll make sure—
Tsukasa: “Next time”? And what about today's audience?!
Tsukasa: There's a different show every day. Each time we perform, we're battling to win over the hearts of the audience. That's why we must succeed each and every time!
Tsukasa: Didn't you all want to make today's show a success?! Or are you going to tell me you didn't care?!
Rui: .....
Nene: It's... It's all my fault...
Nene: It's because I was...too scared to perform in person. I shouldn't have relied on a robot...
Rui: Nene...
Tsukasa: So you admit it?! I should've known there was something wrong with you, staying hidden and only talking to us through a robot!
Tsukasa: So you're a shy girl? Not good with public performances? You think that's an excuse?! If you can't even face your audience, how can you put on a good show?!
Nene: !!
Rui: Tsukasa, stop it.
Nene: ...sorry...
Nene: I'm s-sorry!
Rui: Nene!
Emu: Nene!
Tsukasa: .....
Rui: Don't you think you went too far?
Rui: You're right that it's impossible to do great shows when one of the actors can't face the audience.
Rui: But you seem to be forgetting about something even more basic.
Rui: You can't stage great shows alone, either.
Tsukasa: !!
Rui: Maybe I'm a hypocrite. I've been performing solo for a long time, after all.
Rui: But since joining this troupe, it's become clearer to me than ever before how much more interesting shows become when you work together.
Rui: Fellow performers should be valued. What are you trying to achieve picking on your colleague who is already feeling terribly guilty over what happened?
Rui: I'm disappointed to see that you don't seem to have a true passion for theater after all.
Tsukasa: No! You're wrong! I put my heart and soul into making our show the best it could be!
Tsukasa: I've always given my all to performances! Always trying my best to one day achieve stardom!
Rui: To achieve stardom, you say?
Rui: Hmph. That's all you care about? So I'm right then.
Rui: To you, theater is just a means of achieving some selfish, personal goal.
Tsukasa: Wait, how can you say that...
Rui: I won't be coming here anymore.
Tsukasa: Huh...
Rui: Oh, and by the way...
Rui: You don't have what it takes to become a star.
Tsukasa: !!
Tsukasa: Why? Why do you think I don't have what it takes?!
Emu: Rui, don't go!
Tsukasa: ...
Emu: Tsukasa, w-wait!
Emu: I just wanted to say I had lots of fun today! I really enjoyed performing in front of an audience!
Emu: That's why... I want to try again! Next time everything will go just fine!
Tsukasa: .....
Emu: Didn't you like being in the show?
Tsukasa: With how it went? NO!
Emu: Tsukasa!
Emu: What now? No one is smiling anymore...
Rui: Nene...
Nene: Oh...
Rui: I'm sorry, Nene. For making you join that troupe. Also, I should've checked the robot's battery.
Nene: ..... No, I... I messed this up...
Nene: Um... Where's Robo-Nene?
Rui: We won't be needing it anymore. I left it back at the stage.
Nene: Huh?
Rui: I won't force you to perform in a show ever again.
Nene: .....
Tsukasa: For crying out loud... Why did it have to end this way?!
Tsukasa: I just...wanted to stage a great show...
Tsukasa: Huh? What was that flash? My...phone?
Tsukasa: It was that song, “Untitled.” Why did it do that?
KAITO: If there's anything else you need help with, you're welcome to visit us anytime.
Tsukasa: .....
Tsukasa: It's so quiet... Where is everyone? Normally Miku and KAITO would come out right away...
???: *Sob*...
Tsukasa: Hm? Is someone crying?
Bunny Plushie: *Sob*... *Sniff*...
Tsukasa: Is that plushie...crying?
